instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin lifecycle for the incubator begins with *Data Acquisition*—continuous readings from two inside temperature sensors and an outside sensor, streamed via the Raspberry Pi to a cloud or local storage. Next is *Model Development*, where two thermal simulation models (one with two free parameters and one with four) are implemented in an open‑source repository (see https://github.com/INTO-CPS-Association/example-incubator). *Model Calibration* follows, utilizing a calibration algorithm that fuses real‑time sensor data with the parameterized models to obtain the most accurate physical–cyber representation. The *Simulation* phase runs the calibrated models to predict future temperature trajectories and evaluate control actions. *Monitoring* then compares simulated predictions with live sensor data, feeding safety and optimality checks back into the system. Finally, *Decision Support* allows human operators or automated supervisors to modify the physical twin (e.g., adjust heater duty cycle) based on detected violations or optimization outputs, thereby completing the loop. Transition management is handled via continuous integration of new sensor data into the model repository, while governance is enforced by version control on GitHub and regular model validation against experimental results."
]

